For Task 3, I explored coding and collaboration platforms to understand their importance in academics. I used HackerRank as a coding practice platform and successfully solved a beginner-level problem called “Solve Me First.” This helped me understand basic programming logic and improved my problem-solving skills.

I also created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Quiz” with five questions to test awareness among students. The form included both multiple-choice and short-answer questions. I explored the responses section, which helps in collecting and analyzing data efficiently.

These platforms are very useful for students. HackerRank helps in improving coding skills and preparing for technical interviews, while Google Forms is helpful for creating surveys, quizzes, and collecting feedback. Overall, this task helped me understand how digital tools can support learning and collaboration in an academic environment.
